title: Week in Pictures: From Pakistan blast to US protests
text:
Most Searched Week in Pictures: From Pakistan blast to US protests From protests in Kenya and the US to a suicide attack in Pakistan, here is the week in pictures. 17 Feb 2017 10:22 GMT 
Turkana tribesmen walk with guns in order to protect their cattle from rival Pokot and Samburu tribesmen near Baragoy, Kenya. [Goran Tomasevic/Reuters] 
A Rohingya refugee girl cries at Leda Unregistered Refugee Camp in Teknaf, Bangladesh. [Mohammad Ponir Hossain/Reuters] 
Demonstrators march on the 'Day Without Immigrants' protest in Washington, DC. [Aaron P Bernstein/Reuters] 
Hussain Zeeno Zannun (r) 26, and Chahad, 16, are Iraqi newlyweds who fled Mosul and are showered in foam during their wedding party at Khazer refugee camp in Iraq. [Zohra Bensemra/Reuters] 
A woman comforts her son, who is suffering from malaria, as they wait for treatment at a Medecins Sans Frontieres (MSF) run clinic in the village of Likuangole, in Boma state, east South Sudan. [Siegfried Modola/Reuters] 
Jeanette Vizguerra, (l), a Mexican woman seeking to avoid deportation from the US, cradles her six-year-old daughter, Zuri, during a news conference in a Denver church where they have taken refuge. US immigration authorities have denied her request to remain in the country. [David Zalubowski/AP Photo] 
Supporters of Iraqi Shia cleric Moqtada al-Sadr gather for a protest demanding an overhaul of the elections supervision commission ahead of provincial elections due in September, in Baghdad, Iraq. [Alaa Al-Marjani /Reuters] 
Indigenous mayors watch from the gallery overlooking Guatemala's Congress, a session to discuss the proposed constitutional amendment to recognise indigenous justice as part of the country's judicial system, in Guatemala City. Guatemala's Constitutional Court already has accepted some rulings by indigenous courts. [Moises Castillo/AP Photo] 
Doctors and medical staff protest the detention of their union leaders outside an appeal court in Nairobi, Kenya. A Kenyan court has released seven doctors who are officials in the medics union and who were jailed earlier this week for not calling off a strike by doctors working in public institutions. [Ben Curtis/AP Photo] 
Volunteers move the body of a victim at the scene of a bomb attack in Peshawar, Pakistan, one of several attacks that rocked the country this week. [Fayaz Aziz/Reuters] Recommended
